# Proposed 0010 — PCI INTx status at post_delay (observation)

English (canonical). **Design sketch** — apply manually at the `post_delay` call site from Phase 7 `0006b-stat-decode.patch` (`snd_repair_phase7_intr_decode` or immediately after `"post_delay"` decode).

**Binary question:** When `STAT1=0x4` at `post_delay`, is PCI config **`PCI_STATUS_INTERRUPT`** (bit 8) set?

---

## Insert (conceptual)

After existing `intr_decode` log for `when == "post_delay"`:

```c
struct pci_dev *pci = to_pci_dev(bus->dev->parent);
u16 pci_status;

if (pci && !pci_read_config_word(pci, PCI_STATUS, &pci_status))
    dev_info(dev,
             "PHASE10 ctx=amd fn=pci_intx when=%s stat1=0x%x pci_status=0x%04x intx=%u\n",
             when, stat1, pci_status,
             !!(pci_status & PCI_STATUS_INTERRUPT));
```

Requires `#include <linux/pci.h>` if not already present.

---

## Interpretation

| Boot @ first SDW1 IRQ | Resume @ post_delay |
|-----------------------|---------------------|
| `stat1=0x4 intx=1` | `stat1=0x4 intx=0` → pin **not** asserted; gap inside ACP/firmware |
| `stat1=0x4 intx=1` | `stat1=0x4 intx=1` → pin asserted; gap **after** PCI (IO-APIC/Linux) |

Capture boot baseline in same build (`journalctl -k -b 0 | grep pci_intx`).

---

## Build

Observation-only on Phase 6 + 0007 + 0008 base. **No** falsification patch stacked.

One suspend cycle: `pre-suspend` → suspend → `post-resume` → grep `PHASE10.*pci_intx`.

